we'll call this contextual semiotics
the semiotic model is sufficient for sings and sign systems
however it lacks interpreters and the location of the signs (where they exist)
This is necessary because semiosis may be handed off between different actors(interpreters) across different realities.
In particular a person may have an imagination that creates a fictional interpreter in a fictional world.  
The interpred sense is handed off out of the imagination back to the person who is imagining.
In which case parts of semiosis have also taken place across fictional and physical realms.